Does he know?

29:46.200 --> 29:48.080
- Know what?

29:49.100 --> 29:50.200
- What happened here?

29:50.200 --> 29:53.220
(suspenseful music)

29:56.130 --> 29:57.220
I take that as a no.

30:02.010 --> 30:06.010
- Timing hasn't really
been great recently.

30:08.010 --> 30:11.090
All he knows is that his grandad
died and left us the house.

30:13.010 --> 30:15.120
- When was the last
time you talked to him?

30:15.120 --> 30:17.200
Your dad. Did you talk
to him before he passed?

30:19.190 --> 30:20.150
- No.

30:22.010 --> 30:24.120
- When was the last
time you talked to him?

30:24.120 --> 30:28.090
- (chuckles) You're full
of questions today, huh?

30:31.200 --> 30:33.080
(liquor sloshes)

30:33.080 --> 30:34.040
- Talk to me.

30:38.080 --> 30:40.000
(both laughing)

30:40.000 --> 30:42.010
Slow down on that stuff.

30:44.070 --> 30:46.020
Oh, oh.
- Oh.

30:47.040 --> 30:49.150
That's the Amy I remember.

30:49.150 --> 30:52.140
- Oh, the excessively
drunk one, huh? (chuckles)

30:52.140 --> 30:55.020
- No. The happy one.

30:56.220 --> 30:58.220
- You're just trying to get me
drunk so I spill my secrets.

30:58.220 --> 31:01.070
- (sighs) I'm just
trying to figure out

31:01.070 --> 31:03.230
what's going on with you.
(Amy sighs)

31:03.230 --> 31:06.030
You leave town after
your dad's trial.

31:07.170 --> 31:11.160
You don't send me a
text, call. Nothing.

31:14.080 --> 31:16.110
Do you keep in
contact with anyone?

31:19.010 --> 31:22.000
I know Eric was asking
about you. (chuckles)

31:22.000 --> 31:23.170
- Eric Salinda?

31:23.170 --> 31:26.130
From high school?
- Yeah, man.

31:26.130 --> 31:28.150
- Ooh.
- He loved you.

31:28.150 --> 31:30.080
- Oh-ho. Mm.
(Jenny laughing)

31:30.080 --> 31:32.140
- I think he's still single.

31:32.140 --> 31:34.060
- And there's probably
a reason for that.

31:34.060 --> 31:36.180
(both laugh)

31:38.170 --> 31:39.140
Cut the shit.

31:43.110 --> 31:44.120
- It's, um...

31:48.230 --> 31:51.000
- (sighs) Come on.

31:52.160 --> 31:55.130
I care about you.
You can talk to me.

31:58.100 --> 32:00.120
- We just didn't have
anywhere else to go.

32:02.040 --> 32:04.070
- Who are you running from?

32:04.070 --> 32:07.120
- Huh. Um...

32:09.230 --> 32:11.040
Her name's Judith.

32:12.180 --> 32:15.150
- Judith? Okay.

32:17.120 --> 32:18.100
Who's Judith?

32:22.080 --> 32:23.070
- Adrian's mom.

32:26.090 --> 32:27.210
- But you are Adrian's mom.

32:27.210 --> 32:31.010
- His other mom.

32:32.210 --> 32:33.170
- Oh. Oh.

32:35.180 --> 32:36.140
- Yeah.

32:38.010 --> 32:40.060
Good Old Kathy
would've should a brick

32:40.060 --> 32:42.220
if she was still alive.
- (laughs) Would've loved

32:42.220 --> 32:44.090
to see her face.
- Hmm-hmm.

32:45.170 --> 32:48.190
No, you would not. (chuckles)

32:48.190 --> 32:52.030
- So you and Judith
adopted Adrian together?

32:54.000 --> 32:55.110
- Yeah, we got lucky.

32:57.160 --> 32:58.140
I got lucky.

33:00.020 --> 33:01.190
- So why are you
running from her?

33:04.030 --> 33:07.100
(Amy sniffs and sighs)

33:08.120 --> 33:11.040
- Holy shit. Are you okay?

33:11.040 --> 33:14.040
- Yeah, just had a, had
a little bit of a fight.

33:15.060 --> 33:17.040
- Do you need to see a doctor?

33:17.040 --> 33:18.180
- I'm fine, it's healing.
- Are you sure?

33:18.180 --> 33:23.020
(exhales) So this Judith
is a bit cray cray?

33:23.020 --> 33:26.180
- Yeah, would've, uh, given
Kathy a run for her money.

33:26.180 --> 33:27.230
- Wow.

33:27.230 --> 33:29.150
(Amy laughs)

33:29.150 --> 33:30.110
- What?

33:31.210 --> 33:33.110
- Didn't you just say cray cray?

33:34.220 --> 33:36.170
- Isn't that what the
kids say these days?

33:36.170 --> 33:38.060
- I have no idea.

33:38.060 --> 33:39.220
(both laugh)

33:39.220 --> 33:41.220
- I'm trying to be serious.

33:41.220 --> 33:43.030
- Sorry. I'm sorry.

33:44.040 --> 33:47.080
(both chuckle)

33:47.080 --> 33:48.230
Fuck. I have missed you.

33:48.230 --> 33:51.100
- (chuckles) I missed you too.

33:58.070 --> 34:00.180
- I'm so fucking sorry for
coming back into your life

34:00.180 --> 34:03.040
a complete shit
show of a disaster.

34:03.040 --> 34:07.000
- Hmm, oh. It's okay. (chuckles)

34:07.000 --> 34:10.080
It was getting kind of
boring around here anyways.

34:10.080 --> 34:11.220
Needed some added spice.

34:11.220 --> 34:12.180
- Like I...

34:14.140 --> 34:17.000
shouldn't having
me just unloading

34:17.000 --> 34:18.070
all of my baggage onto you.

34:18.070 --> 34:19.200
You have your own life.

34:21.140 --> 34:24.220
- Look, I wouldn't be
here if I didn't wanna be.

34:27.060 --> 34:30.010
- (inhales) Thank you.

34:34.150 --> 34:39.150
(both chuckle)
(glass clink)

34:40.100 --> 34:42.080
(Jenny exhales)

34:42.080 --> 34:43.200
Hey, I, um,

34:43.200 --> 34:45.100
I really appreciate
you coming by

34:45.100 --> 34:47.140
and basically feeding
us for the next month.

34:47.140 --> 34:50.080
- Oh, it's what I'm
here for. (chuckles)

34:50.080 --> 34:54.050
- Um, I actually have
something for you. Just...

35:04.100 --> 35:05.140
(Jenny laughs)
(Amy exhales)

35:05.140 --> 35:07.100
Found it in the basement.

35:07.100 --> 35:09.050
- Look at us. Uh.

35:10.070 --> 35:12.010
- It's like peas in a pod.

35:12.010 --> 35:13.040
- Something like that.

35:13.040 --> 35:15.000
(both chuckle)

35:15.000 --> 35:19.040
(sighs) Well, I
better get going.

35:19.040 --> 35:20.160
Hubby's gonna be calling soon.

35:26.120 --> 35:29.050
(soft dramatic music)

35:29.050 --> 35:33.200
Well, I will be back in a few
days to check on you guys.

35:33.200 --> 35:34.160
- Sounds good.

35:36.000 --> 35:36.200
Drive safely.

35:38.200 --> 35:41.110
(exhales) Fuck.

35:41.110 --> 35:43.230
(pounds fist)

35:47.080 --> 35:50.030
(fire crackling)

35:51.140 --> 35:54.130
- Mom, why are we always
sleeping on the floor?

35:55.140 --> 35:57.190
(Amy takes deep breath)

35:57.190 --> 36:00.090
- I guess I should get
a mattress. Shouldn't I?

36:00.090 --> 36:01.130
- That would be cozier.

36:03.200 --> 36:04.190
- I'll get on that.

36:06.070 --> 36:07.220
See if I can get one
from Jenny tomorrow.

36:09.170 --> 36:11.170
- I wish there was one in
the bedroom that we can use.

36:11.170 --> 36:14.100
- Mm, no, that one was
tossed out years ago.

36:15.150 --> 36:17.010
- Was it gross?

36:17.010 --> 36:20.100
(soft dramatic music)

36:20.100 --> 36:22.130
- It had cooties.
- Ew.

36:22.130 --> 36:24.200
- (chuckles) Yeah.

36:24.200 --> 36:26.130
Now go to sleep.

36:26.130 --> 36:28.130
- Okay, Mom. I love you.

36:28.130 --> 36:32.160
(soft dramatic music continues)

36:42.080 --> 36:44.070
(fire crackling)

36:44.070 --> 36:47.070
(crickets chirping)

37:13.090 --> 37:16.110
(suspenseful music)

37:38.230 --> 37:39.190
Hello?

37:42.180 --> 37:43.180
Who are you?

37:45.100 --> 37:47.050
How'd you get in here?

37:48.070 --> 37:50.060
Get out, get out my house!

37:51.140 --> 37:53.050
Get out!

37:53.050 --> 37:54.220
Go away!
(Amy gasps)

37:54.220 --> 37:56.030
Stop!

37:56.030 --> 37:57.130
- Adrian!
- Stop!

37:57.130 --> 37:59.230
Get out of my house! Go away!

38:01.050 --> 38:03.090
Stop! Get out of my house!

38:04.200 --> 38:06.010
Get out of my house!
- Adrian, Adrian,

38:06.010 --> 38:07.150
who's here?
- Get out!

38:07.150 --> 38:09.210
- Baby, wake up, wake up!
- Get out!

38:09.210 --> 38:11.030
- Baby, what's wrong?

38:12.150 --> 38:15.000
- There was someone right there.

38:15.000 --> 38:17.080
- Baby, baby,
there's no one there.

38:17.080 --> 38:18.040
It's okay.

38:19.150 --> 38:22.100
We're alone. You're safe.

38:22.100 --> 38:25.100
(suspenseful music)

38:36.170 --> 38:38.090
(train rumbling)

38:38.090 --> 38:40.230
(horn blaring)

38:44.140 --> 38:47.210
♪ You better kill me dead ♪

38:47.210 --> 38:51.010
♪ For they were
born to lose again ♪

38:51.010 --> 38:54.110
♪ You better run,
you better run ♪

38:54.110 --> 38:55.210
♪ I have a gun ♪

38:55.210 --> 38:57.190
♪ I'll beat you up ♪

38:57.190 --> 39:00.200
♪ You better run,
you better run ♪

39:00.200 --> 39:02.190
♪ I'll beat you up ♪

39:02.190 --> 39:04.040
♪ You better run ♪

39:04.040 --> 39:06.160
(birds chirping)

39:06.160 --> 39:09.080
(water flowing)

39:11.140 --> 39:16.150
(blade clicking)
(tense music)

39:38.210 --> 39:40.210
(knife whooshes and whacks)

39:40.210 --> 39:42.230
(chimes jingling)

39:42.230 --> 39:45.140
(gun fires)

39:45.140 --> 39:48.000
(gun clacks)

39:50.020 --> 39:52.100
(gun fires)

39:53.200 --> 39:56.060
(gun clacks)

39:59.050 --> 40:01.120
(gun fires)

40:01.120 --> 40:03.110
- You gonna teach
me how to hunt?

40:03.110 --> 40:04.170
- Sure. Come here for a sec.

40:04.170 --> 40:07.060
(gun clacks)

40:07.060 --> 40:11.020
Okay. Now stand about there.

40:12.000 --> 40:13.090
See the target?

40:13.090 --> 40:15.100
Okay. Little bit down.

40:16.090 --> 40:17.060
Perfect.

40:19.000 --> 40:21.050
You're gonna gently put
your finger on the trigger.

40:21.050 --> 40:22.180
(gun fires)

40:22.180 --> 40:24.130
(dog barking)

40:24.130 --> 40:27.060
Oh, hey, it's okay.
It's okay, come here.

40:27.060 --> 40:28.060
We'll just do it one more time.

40:28.060 --> 40:29.200
- I don't want to.

40:29.200 --> 40:31.000
- Oh, come on baby. It's easy.

40:31.000 --> 40:32.010
Let's do it one more time.

40:32.010 --> 40:32.210
- No.

40:32.210 --> 40:34.190
(tense music)

40:34.190 --> 40:36.070
- Get over here. Oh.

40:41.040 --> 40:44.120
(Amy takes deep breath)

40:45.100 --> 40:50.090
Hey, I'm sorry, okay?

40:50.090 --> 40:55.080
I just, just wanna be
able to protect you.

40:55.080 --> 40:56.060
- From her?

40:59.080 --> 41:01.020
- Yeah, from her,

41:02.160 --> 41:05.020
or anyone else who
might try to hurt you

41:05.020 --> 41:06.080
or take you away from me.

41:08.150 --> 41:09.110
- Okay.

41:10.180 --> 41:13.050
- Yeah? Okay.

41:14.100 --> 41:16.120
(gun clacks)

41:16.120 --> 41:17.100
You ready? Here.

41:19.190 --> 41:21.090
Stand a little bit more down.

41:22.160 --> 41:26.080
And whenever you're ready.

41:26.080 --> 41:28.130
(gun fires)

41:28.130 --> 41:30.160
Baby, that was amazing!

41:30.160 --> 41:33.100
Nice shot! Baby, you did it!

41:33.100 --> 41:36.070
(suspenseful music)
That is awesome.

41:36.070 --> 41:37.090
Let's go check it out.

41:43.100 --> 41:46.120
(crickets chirping)

41:50.000 --> 41:51.070
There you go, sweetie.

41:56.050 --> 41:57.190
Eat up.

41:57.190 --> 41:59.090
- I'm just not that hungry.

42:02.190 --> 42:04.020
- Baby, you love chicken.

42:12.030 --> 42:14.210
You know, we're really
lucky to have this food.

42:14.210 --> 42:16.130
- I know.
- Then eat.

42:31.100 --> 42:34.000
- You think she's
coming here, don't you?

42:34.000 --> 42:36.030
That's why you have the gun.

42:36.030 --> 42:38.070
She's gonna take me away.

42:38.070 --> 42:40.010
- Eat your fucking food.

42:40.010 --> 42:42.020
(tense music)

42:42.020 --> 42:43.110
Adrian, come back here.

42:44.210 --> 42:47.050
(Amy sighs)

43:13.040 --> 43:16.120
(tense music continues)

43:36.160 --> 43:39.140
(plate clattering)

43:45.010 --> 43:49.020
(door opens and creaks)

43:49.020 --> 43:52.020
(suspenseful music)

44:00.110 --> 44:03.010
(door creaks)

44:23.080 --> 44:24.040
Adrian.

44:26.100 --> 44:29.040
(switch clicks)

44:30.150 --> 44:32.070
Bubba, I'm sorry
I snapped at you.

44:40.100 --> 44:42.040
Turn around, I'm talking to you.

44:43.060 --> 44:45.120
(Amy gasping and groaning)

44:45.120 --> 44:49.150
(slapping and cracking)

44:49.150 --> 44:51.040
- Mom!

44:51.040 --> 44:52.160
(Amy groaning)
Stop!

44:52.160 --> 44:54.100
(thumping)

44:54.100 --> 44:57.020
(intense music)

45:08.190 --> 45:10.150
(birds chirping)

45:10.150 --> 45:13.130
(chimes jingling)

45:36.040 --> 45:37.080
- Hey, baby.

45:38.050 --> 45:39.010
- Hey, Mom.

45:41.090 --> 45:42.070
- Oh, fuck.

45:48.130 --> 45:49.170
What happened?

45:52.190 --> 45:54.040
Adrian, what happened?

45:55.100 --> 45:56.230
- You don't remember?

45:56.230 --> 45:59.110
(tense music)

46:01.230 --> 46:06.050
(Amy groans and
breathes uneasily)

46:10.190 --> 46:15.200
(finger cracking)
(Amy gasping)

46:19.130 --> 46:22.160
(tense music)

46:22.160 --> 46:26.020
(Amy breathes uneasily)

46:33.110 --> 46:37.100
- The last thing I remember
was chasing you in here.

46:37.100 --> 46:41.130
(tense music continues)

46:41.130 --> 46:43.230
(Amy sighs)

46:47.130 --> 46:48.110
Thank you, baby.

47:04.160 --> 47:07.220
(Amy sighs)

47:07.220 --> 47:08.180
Adrian.

47:15.010 --> 47:16.210
What happened last night?

47:16.210 --> 47:17.190
- I don't know.

47:19.030 --> 47:20.060
- Who did this to me?

47:22.200 --> 47:25.100
Tell me.
- Stop, you're hurting me!

47:25.100 --> 47:28.000
(eerie music)

47:30.080 --> 47:31.080
- I'm sorry.

47:35.050 --> 47:38.230
Was someone in our house? Who?

47:40.010 --> 47:42.010
- I, I could barely see them.

47:43.050 --> 47:44.090
- Mean you can barely see them?

47:44.090 --> 47:45.210
You were in the room with me.

47:47.100 --> 47:48.180
- They were hard to see.

47:50.230 --> 47:52.230
- Have you seen them
in the house before?

47:57.200 --> 47:59.230
(sighs) Must be a
squatter or something.

47:59.230 --> 48:01.130
- Squatter?

48:01.130 --> 48:03.130
- Yeah, hey have to
be getting in somehow.

48:04.220 --> 48:05.180
- Mom.

48:07.050 --> 48:08.190
- What?

48:08.190 --> 48:09.210
- I wanna leave.

48:12.060 --> 48:15.070
- And where the hell
are we gonna go, Adrian?

48:15.070 --> 48:18.080
We are miles away from town.
My phone is smashed to shit.

48:18.080 --> 48:20.150
So no, we're not
fucking leaving!

48:20.150 --> 48:21.150
We're stuck!

48:21.150 --> 48:24.030
(tense music)

48:30.220 --> 48:33.180
(hammer banging)

48:37.010 --> 48:41.010
(sighs) Okay, I don't want you
coming in this room anymore.

48:41.010 --> 48:43.050
And do not answer the
front door for anyone.

48:43.050 --> 48:44.190
Even Jenny.

48:44.190 --> 48:45.190
- I promise.

48:46.210 --> 48:47.220
- I'm gonna keep us safe.

48:49.000 --> 48:52.070
(dog barking in distance)

48:52.070 --> 48:57.070
(eerie music)
(water trickling)

49:10.170 --> 49:12.230
- You didn't wash your
face like I asked.

49:12.230 --> 49:14.190
- I'm sorry, Mom.

49:14.190 --> 49:17.070
- I know, but you
always say you're sorry

49:17.070 --> 49:19.060
after I've asked
you a hundred times.

49:19.060 --> 49:20.080
- Are you mad?

49:21.180 --> 49:22.150
- I'm not mad.

49:24.100 --> 49:26.140
- I want you to remember
something very important.

49:28.070 --> 49:32.180
It's my job to keep
you well-fed, clean,

49:32.180 --> 49:34.200
obedient and beautiful.

49:36.020 --> 49:37.200
Beauty's a fragile thing.

49:37.200 --> 49:40.150
Like porcelain doll
or a China plate.

49:42.030 --> 49:44.020
One false move and it
can all just shatter.

49:44.020 --> 49:47.100
(eerie music continues)

49:52.090 --> 49:55.050
(water trickling)

49:58.160 --> 50:01.060
(faucet thuds)

50:07.000 --> 50:09.220
(knocking on door)

50:21.210 --> 50:25.010
(knocking continues)

50:29.060 --> 50:31.170
- Who is it?
- It's Jenny.

50:31.170 --> 50:33.210
Open the door.
It's hot out here.

50:37.170 --> 50:39.230
- Hey.
- Hey, you guys okay?

50:39.230 --> 50:41.200
I've been trying to call.

50:41.200 --> 50:43.160
I was on my way to work,
so I figured I'd stop by.

50:43.160 --> 50:45.220
- Oh, um, yeah.
Uh, my phone broke.

50:45.220 --> 50:47.150
(chuckles nervously) Sorry.

50:47.150 --> 50:50.060
- Are you, are you okay?

50:50.060 --> 50:52.040
- Oh yeah. Yeah,
we're, we're fine.

50:53.230 --> 50:55.180
- I know when you're being
a total bullshit artist.

51:00.110 --> 51:03.080
Holy shit. What happened?

51:03.080 --> 51:05.210
- It's fine. It's just
some bruises, seriously.

51:08.100 --> 51:11.080
- Be honest with
me. Was she here?

51:11.080 --> 51:13.170
- No, no. Uh, no, no.

51:13.170 --> 51:15.150
My, my clumsy ass
just fell off a ladder

51:15.150 --> 51:17.160
fixing some lights in
the master bedroom.

51:19.100 --> 51:20.220
I did have some of that
Wild Turkey you brought by,

51:20.220 --> 51:24.080
but you know, my
face broke the fall.

51:26.130 --> 51:28.210
I am kind of saying that
it was inadvertently

51:28.210 --> 51:30.110
your fault from the...

51:33.040 --> 51:34.180
That was a joke.

51:34.180 --> 51:35.220
- Is that what happened?

51:39.160 --> 51:42.000
- Um, we were actually
about to sit down

51:42.000 --> 51:44.010
and have some dinner,
beef casserole.

51:45.030 --> 51:46.160
- I'm gonna be late for work.

51:46.160 --> 51:48.200
I was just stopping
to check on you guys.

51:48.200 --> 51:50.030
- Yeah. Yeah, okay.

51:51.110 --> 51:52.210
- Thank you for the offer.

51:54.060 --> 51:56.000
Lay off the Wild Turkey.

51:56.000 --> 51:57.020
(Amy chuckles)
Okay?

51:58.150 --> 51:59.100
- Yes, ma'am.

52:00.120 --> 52:01.160
- I'll be back in a few days

52:01.160 --> 52:03.040
with a new burner phone for you.

52:03.040 --> 52:04.080
I don't like you
guys being out here

52:04.080 --> 52:05.080
without a way to call anyone.

52:05.080 --> 52:06.130
- (chuckles) Thank you.

52:08.070 --> 52:10.170
- All right. Bye.

52:10.170 --> 52:11.130
- Bye.

52:15.200 --> 52:20.190
(Amy exhales)
(tense music)

52:20.190 --> 52:23.130
(birds chirping)

52:38.120 --> 52:41.130
(door closes)

52:41.130 --> 52:44.050
(ominous music)

52:51.230 --> 52:54.210
(traffic whirring)

52:59.170 --> 53:03.090
(suspenseful music)

53:03.090 --> 53:06.050
(car door closes)

53:07.210 --> 53:10.200
(lighter clicking)

53:17.170 --> 53:20.170
(crickets chirping)

53:22.200 --> 53:24.150
(customers chattering)

53:24.150 --> 53:26.070
- Hey, Grace. (chuckles)

53:26.070 --> 53:29.090
(upbeat rock music)

53:30.110 --> 53:32.080
What would you like to order?

53:32.080 --> 53:35.210
- I'll have the French toast,
side of bacon and a coffee.

